            Center</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>ElectricFlow Integration to Heroku</h2>
        <!-- The integration description should answer the questions:

                How deep does our integration go? Why should I care? What general

                functionality does the plugin include? What functionality does

                the plugin omit?

                -->
        <!--p>@PLUGIN_KEY@ plugin calls the Heroku web services via HTTP Requests
                    and passes the user-provided parameters.</p-->

        <p>The @PLUGIN_KEY@ plugin is open, it allows the input of
        many Heroku functions defined in the provided fields of the
        parameters. Is important to provide all the parameters
        required for the correct functioning of the Heroku
        plugin.</p>

        <p>ElectricFlow itself provides some advantages like
        parameters checking, easy functionality selection using
        only check boxes or radio buttons, hitorical log reports,
        procedure duration statistics, simple credentials
        attachment, real time analysis of the log been generated,
        among others.</p>

        <h2>Integrated Version</h2>

        <p>This plugin was developed and tested against Heroku
        version 2.31.4 (ruby v.1.9.2)</p>

